      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BIG CUTIE (2) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish 1.75 lengths away in second (17.59) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Rates highly and will give a great sight. NOAH'S MEKONG (5) was fast away from wide out with an impressive early sectional and went on to clock 17.41 in a 3 length win at this track over 300m. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. One of the key runners again. TRALEE DIGBY (4) has been hard to follow lately, running fourth (17.72) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Well placed here and can atone this time. BUGLE GIRL (1) generally performs well from this box.",
